item.title: About
item.dc:creator: laura battermann
item.content:encoded:
Hi there, my name is Laura. To me personally It is very important to be part of a team and to support it in every aspect. With my sunny mind and my openness, paired with German punctuality and reliability I could fit in and convince of myself in every team so far. In various internships and jobs I have worked a lot with people and especially children and thus acquired the right sensitivity and the right way of contact. Through many stays abroad, I not only learned to appreciate other cultures, but also to master even the most difficult situations with an open heart, a smile on my face, the necessary seriousness and still a lot of calmness.

Go to CV

"Living on the sunny side"

Studying Graphic Design at the Florence Institute of Design International and graduating with a Bachelor of Arts from 2016 to 2019.

University The Florence Institute of Design

Designing a Catalogue for the fire architect Stefan Schinharl. From the first layout to the finished printed catalogue I accompanied and supervised every step. 

Freelance Work Kaminmanufaktur Schinharl

Due to a lot of freedom I was able to work on various projects during this internship. From the design of a catalogue to the supervision of social media platforms and the organisation of an event, everything was included.

Graphicdesign Internship Remo Fliesenhandels GmbH

Dealing with the normal challenges of high school life and mastering them. After twelve years of school, I graduated with the Abitur.

Highschool Edith-Stein-Gymnasium München Facebook Pinterest Instagram
